  "texts": [
    "The top row confirms that positron and photon showers are easier to generate than pion showers.",
    "The question is which potential failures are related to this performance difference.In the second row we show the weight distributions.",
    "First, we observe that they are not symmetric, because the reweighting now compensates features.",
    "The limit w(x) = 0, most visible for the pion shower, marks phase space points where the generator has learned a finite density p model (x), where the correct density is p data (x) = 0, one of the typical failure mode of generative models discussed in Sec. 2.",
    "We will see this more clearly for LHC events in the next section, but mention here that it is not catastrophic if we can enforce corresponding phase space boundaries during generation.In the third row of Fig. 4 we show the same curves on a logarithmic scale to see the tails."
